  "lines": [
    {
      "lineNumber": 1,
      "text": "August 8, 1947",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 2,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 3,
      "text": "FLYING DISCS",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 4,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 5,
      "text": "Information was received from the Dow Chemical Company, Midland,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 6,
      "text": "Michigan, that on July 10, 1947, one [REDACTED] an employee of",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 7,
      "text": "Dow Chemical Company since about 1922, brought some material to their",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 8,
      "text": "Physics laboratory. He stated that about 5:15 p.m., July 9, he and his",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 9,
      "text": "wife, Laura, were walking in a field when they heard a puff noise about",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 10,
      "text": "one hundred feet away. They turned and saw a ball of white about the size",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 11,
      "text": "of a bushel basket burning approximately a foot off of the ground. The fire",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 12,
      "text": "died out immediately and later Lane scooped up a three inch area of fused",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 13,
      "text": "sand into a can for examination at their laboratory.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 14,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 15,
      "text": "Upon interview by FBI Agents, [REDACTED] told substantially the same",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 16,
      "text": "story, but [REDACTED] was reluctant to talk and very indefinite about what",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 17,
      "text": "happened. There were marked discrepancies in their stories.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 18,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "text": "Dow authorities considered the story fantastic but have examined",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 20,
      "text": "the material and state contents are: ordinary sand, not radio active, but",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "text": "giving off ammonia gas; a small silver nugget almost pure except for sand",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "text": "mixed in it, not radio active; molted or fused sand which gives off ammonia",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "text": "odor and little droplets of silver melted in sand and some grayish color",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 24,
      "text": "material which is radio active. The level of radio activity in this material",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 25,
      "text": "is extremely low. An employee of Dow, formerly employed by the Government at",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 26,
      "text": "Los Alamos Project, stated the fused sand has some characteristics of Los Alamos",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 27,
      "text": "sand, but he does not believe it is the same.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 28,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 29,
      "text": "[REDACTED] is known to have in his possession a small quantity of",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 30,
      "text": "luminous paint, radio active, to be an amateur photographer and to have a",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 31,
      "text": "limited knowledge of chemistry and physics. He is described as very peculiar,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 32,
      "text": "surly, antagonistic to plant protection officers and interested in photography",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 33,
      "text": "and electricity. Lane is white, was born May 7, 1902, at Freesoil, Michigan.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 34,
      "text": "He is 5' 9\", weighs 145 pounds, has dark brown hair, partly bald, served in",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 35,
      "text": "the U.S. Army from 1918 to 1923. [REDACTED]",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 36,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 37,
      "text": "Neither [REDACTED] will admit their story is a prank.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 38,
      "text": "However, neither are able to point out the exact location of this incident.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 39,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 40,
      "text": "The Army Airforce Intelligence at Selfridge Field, Michigan, has been",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 41,
      "text": "advised and the material has been turned over to them.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
